  "title": "Aurelius, Meditations §aur_04_vi: Such and such things, from such and such causes, must of necessity proceed.",
  "body": "Such and such things, from such and such causes, must of necessity proceed. He that would not have such things to happen, is as he that would have the fig-tree grow without any sap or moisture. In sum, remember this, that within a very little while, both thou and he shall both be dead, and after a little while more, not so much as your names and memories shall be remaining.",
